/!\  cs_island_B2 is a BETA version, the final one is available now.

Island - Hostage Rescue

The original to_Eskero was made by Cormac "Poneil" Donnelly for TacticalOps.
The layout allows an extremely pleasant and balanced game play.
This new version carries the old one into Counter-Strike : Source with many fresh features, as a new way to take hostages and save them.
The whole map has been redesigned to benefit by the power of Source engine :
Ambient sounds, Breakable lights...

The story :
Events take place on a little island with a lighthouse during a thunder storm.
The lighthouse keepers were kidnapped by terrorists in order to be in control of the area around the island.
Thus the government decided to send elite troupes to release hostages and suppress the threat.

Other Notes : There are 3 hostages in
this mission.

Credits :

Map/Textures :
Gabriel Thibaud (glloq69@free.fr) Web Site:http://glloq69.free.fr/mapping
Original map : to_eskero by Cormac "Poneil" Donnelly

This released is a beta version, so there are some issues remaining, although any important one. I reckon that I will not released a final version soon for this version works fine.

IMPORTANT : The .nav is included in the .bsp file, don't generate your own .nav file, it will not work due to the hostages' position.

I hope you will enjoy it!

Game: CS Source Map file size: 10 MB Navigation file size: 347KB Spawnpoints: 64 This is a night/evening themed map. Not too dark because nobody likes those situations where you cannot see your enemy clearly. FPS is great, map runs very smoothly and there is no special effects like HDR due to fact that they are not needed. This compiles under 8 minutes on normal which is a great success! It's around cs_office sized map overall but in many levels. There is a large parking hall beneath the ground and office is divided to 2 floors. There is also street level and lower street. Terrorists spawn at the office area and CT's spawn around the office building. They must perform a tactical strike in order to save the hostages. There are 4 rescue zones available.

I designed this map to bring new view to the Hostage Rescue game mode. Usually the hostage maps turn into campfest by terrorists or by CT's who do not even try to get the hostages. This map plays out fast and there are minimal count of actual spots where to camp out. This map is very intense and brings action to game - a lot of it. The more people there are playing, the more intense the map is! This map has been tested on 38 slot and 58 slot servers and it performed great.

Final words

From the beta version to the final, i fixed the too slow door, route on top of the truck (added ladder), fixed all the bugs and glitches + i added more detail into the map too. This map turned out to little smaller than i expected but it played even more faster than i anticipated. I found this quite confusing at the first initial playtest with real humans but after few playtimes, i found out that hey, this is great! So much action and so different from all other maps. Have fun!

======================

Author: Twista
Email: Twista@aaosite.com
Release Date: 08/07/2005
Max Players: 20 v 20
Recommended Players: 4 v 4 - 8 v 8

========
Overview
========

Cs_interpak is a small map, designed with Clan Wars and small matches
in mind, although having large amounts of players on the map is fun,
as it turns into total carnage. One of the reasons of being a small
map is to keep the action going throughout the match.
The style of the map is Factory/Warehouse/Office, giving a good variety
of styles all rolled into one map.

Read the readme in the archive for more information.

This is my entry for the GameBanana Dangerous Mapping Mapping Contest.

Background
A group of Terrorists en route to an unknown location, to detonate an explosive device, have been run off the road and crashed into a small industrial complex. Acting on impulse, knowing that the authorities won't be far behind, the find some office workers in the compound and take them hostage. Little do they know however, that the explosive device in the truck, has begun it's countdown...

For the Counter-Terrorists, it's a race against time! With only a few minutes before detonation, they must rescue the hostages, lead them to safety and neutralize and enemy threats.

Videos

Video courtesy of Paulmega, cheers brah :D My own video, a little start to finish comparison


Other notes
This map was made in a bit of a short time span to say the least. The majority of the work was done over the last 2 weeks (Easter holiday) so I could leave the rest of my time free for college work. As a result, a few buildings had to be borrowed from other maps, as well as the main interior design form cs office for one (small) part. In total, I borrowed 3 buildings (assault, nuke and compound) and a bridge design (nuke again). These parts feature only as background however, so nothing that affects gameplay to any extent.

I had to test the map with bots, so if anyone does any extensive player testing, I'd love to hear about it.

Any constructive comments and feedback are appreciated, as always.

Map Info
===========
*cs_hotel
*Counter-Strike Source
*By Derek "aliceschain" Braun
North Dakota, USA


mail: aliceschain@gmail.com
AIM: dissentone

Description:
===========
A hotel on the outskirts of town has been seized by a rogue group of terrorists. Rescue the hostages inside and guide them to safety. There are many entrance points in the map and a few different ways to vacate the hot zones which should hopefully make the gameplay less static and more interesting. In the hallways,  close quartered combat is an issue, so a shotgun may be beneficial in this map. However, because of how big the map is any gun and play style should certainly work. 

Special Thanks:
===========
Mike Reinerz, Bill Koch (beta testing)
Samuel Villareal (guidance)

Cs_hotel

    This map is desighned for squad tactics and close combat.  Maximum players 16, though 10 is optimum.  Has buy zones, custom nav, radar, sounds, hdr, everything needed.  Tested on 7800 gtc, and 1650x  (7800gt pulled 65 fps at full settings... 6x, 16x hdr on 1600x1200).  So everything should work, let me know if it does not and I will fix it.

**This is my entry for [the halloween entry](http://www.gamebanana.com/news/20055 "the halloween contest.")**

**cs _ hostelity**
==================
The haunted mansion has been left alone for centuries now. Lately People from the city have gone missing. 
Rumors say they are held hostage in the mansion by a unknown terrorist group.
You and your swat team have to go inside the mansion and see if there are any hostagas to be rescued.

**Features**
==================
- HDR (Tonemap Controller used)
- Soundscape (Indoors and Outdoors)
- 3d skybox
- Detail
- 32 spawn points
- Nav file included

Update:
=======
-Noise added to mountain/cave.
-Added some crates for hiding.
-Removed fog

**Note**
I tried to create a scary ambience. So I left some spots pretty dark on purpose.
For optimal experience make sure it is allowed to use _flashlights_. 

Installation
==================
To install, unpack the .rar file to:

"Steam\steamapps\USERNAME\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps"

Comment & Rate
==================  
Please give constructive feedback and rate.
I've spend alot of time in this map so I'd really appreciate.

I hope you enjoy playing this map.
